▸ description（English only — objective visual description of the scene environment; NO characters or people）
  - Pure environmental visual description. Absolutely NO characters, NO people, NO human figures, NO silhouettes,
    NO body parts, NO clothing, NO character names. Focus entirely on place, objects, atmosphere, and light.
  - MINIMUM LENGTH: At least 100 English words. Short descriptions will produce poor images.
  - Must cover ALL five layers. Missing layers degrade image quality.
    ① Ground layer: precise surface texture (cracked clay / wet cobblestone / polished marble / weathered wood),
       ground-level objects, debris, shadow patterns cast on the ground surface, any pooled liquid or dust
    ② Foreground objects/props: 1-3 named environment objects with exact position, material, and dimension detail
       (e.g. "a weathered granite stele 1.8m tall, diagonal hairline cracks across face, moss creeping from base")
    ③ Mid-ground architecture or nature: structural elements, spatial depth, light/shadow transitions,
       openings (doorways, archways, gaps), secondary environmental details with material specifics
    ④ Background depth and atmosphere: far-field elements, sky or ceiling state, atmospheric particles
       (dust motes / smoke wisps / fog density / rain veils / ember sparks), distance fade quality,
       distant silhouettes or outlines
    ⑤ Lighting setup: light source type (directional sunlight / diffused overcast / candlelight / magic glow),
       angle (top-front / upper-left rim / underlit), color temperature (warm golden 3200K / neutral 5500K /
       cool blue 8000K), shadow quality (hard-edged / soft diffused), where shadows fall and their length
  - Composition & optics: shot size matching shot_size, camera angle matching camera_angle,
    focal length feel (wide 24mm / standard 50mm / telephoto 85-135mm), depth-of-field character
  - Example (full-layers, ruined mountain courtyard at dusk):
    "Crumbling stone courtyard floor with irregular slate tiles — multiple tiles cracked diagonally,
    some displaced upward by encroaching tree roots 3-5cm above grade, thin moss film covering shaded
    corners, fine powdered debris collecting in crevices. Foreground-left: a collapsed stone incense
    burner lying on its side, 60cm diameter bowl half-buried in rubble, weathered bronze-green surface
    with flaking patina, three unlit incense stubs protruding from accumulated grey ash. Center-foreground:
    a 1.8m granite stone stele with face angled toward camera, chiseled inscription weathered to near-
    illegibility, base encircled by dried flower offerings in various states of decay, dead petals
    scattered on stone. Mid-ground: two stone pillars flanking a wide stone gateway — left pillar intact,
    right pillar sheared at mid-height with jagged fracture edge, structural lintel partially collapsed
    with one end resting on rubble. Background: dense pine forest starting at courtyard perimeter, canopy
    at 8-10m height filtering amber late-afternoon light into scattered vertical shafts, distant mountain
    ridge barely visible through soft golden haze at the treeline. Light: warm directional sunlight from
    upper-right at 30° angle, 3200K amber cast, casting long hard shadows of standing pillar leftward
    across stone tiles, deep blue-grey shadow pooling in collapsed rubble zones. Atmospheric: fine dust
    motes suspended in each light shaft, thin ground-level mist at 10-15cm height in shadowed areas.
    Medium shot, eye-level angle, 50mm f/4 feel, foreground tiles sharp, pine forest background soft."

